BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:gxTBuj1Kk5HBG7Fih4O8s
SUMMARY:Issaquah Drink N' Draw
DTSTAMP:20260315T172855Z
DTSTART:20260317T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:ISSAQUAH'S LOCAL ART MEETUP Calling all artists and art enthusi
	asts! Join us for an evening filled with creativity\, camaraderie\, and\, 
	of course\, drinks at your local Issaquah Drink n' Draw! Location: Formula
	 Brewing\, 1875 NW Poplar Way\, Issaquah\, WA 98027 Indulge your artistic 
	side in a relaxed and social setting. Whether you're a seasoned artist or 
	just starting your creative journey\, this event is the perfect opportunit
	y to: Draw: Bring your sketchbooks\, pencils\, tablets\, or any medium of 
	your choice. As long as it can fit in a 2' x 2' space and can be cleaned u
	p easily\, we welcome art of all types! Unleash your imagination and creat
	e alongside like-minded individuals. Let your creativity flow!  Don't know
	 what to draw? Search the hashtag \\#essdrawmonthly or find the latest pin
	ned Prompt List on the ESS group page! ️ Chat: Engage in lively conversatio
	ns with fellow artists. Share tips\, techniques\, and stories while gettin
	g inspired by each other's work. Connect with a diverse community passiona
	te about art. Drink: Sip on your favorite beverages from Formula's selecti
	on of refreshments. Whether it's a cold beer\, a glass of wine\, or a non-
	alcoholic option\, enjoy a drink while you immerse yourself in the creativ
	e process. ✏️ This event is open to artists of all skill levels and backgro
	unds. Feel free to join us solo or invite friends to share in this artisti
	c experience. Admission is FREE. Seating is first-come\, first-served. Whi
	le there's usually enough table space\, if we get too busy\, you may have 
	to spread out. Come and be a part of this vibrant artistic gathering! Let'
	s sketch\, chat\, and create memorable art together. We can't wait to see 
	your masterpieces! For more information\, contact group organizers Blayne 
	Fox and Kat Klockow. Note: Remember to drink responsibly and be mindful of
	 others' space and creativity during the event.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcit
	y.com/events/#/details/issaquah-drink-n-draw/16132606/2026-03-16T00\n\nFro
	m SEAtoday - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/issaquah-drink-n-draw/161
	32606/2026-03-16T00
LOCATION:Formula Brewing\, 1875 NW Poplar Way\, Issaquah\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:1F_jupWclRTqr4CnIJjK2
SUMMARY:Liveable Kirkland Meetup -- Project: Build Whistle Kits
DTSTAMP:20260315T172855Z
DTSTART:20260317T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Liveable Kirkland Meetups Mon\, Feb 16\, Mar 2\, Mar 16\, 6-8pm
	 Chainline Brewing at Kirkland Urban For this special series of Meetups\, 
	we'll kick off our usual socials with an ICE-breaker activity -- assemblin
	g whistle kits. These kits will contain a tiny whistle\, a "Know Your Righ
	ts" card\, and instructions on what to do and who to call if you see ICE A
	ctivity.  After assembling whistle kits\, we'll socialize as usual.  We'll
	 get to know one another and chat about local events and issues\, probably
	 including things like homes for everyone\, sustainability\, people-orient
	ed communities\, and ways to improve the quality of life in Kirkland for e
	veryone.  Drop in and bring friends\, family\, and neighbors! Okay to brin
	g kids and food\, too.  Follow all of Liveable Kirkland's events: On our c
	alendar: https://www.liveablekirkland.org/calendar On Meetup: https://www.
	meetup.com/liveablekirkland/ And connect with us on Discord\, Facebook\, a
	nd subscribe to our weekly newsletter here: https://www.liveablekirkland.o
	rg/join\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/liveable-kirkland
	-meetup-project-build-whistle-kits/18291035/2026-03-16T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday
	 - Food & Drink
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/liveable-kirkland-meetup-
	project-build-whistle-kits/18291035/2026-03-16T00
LOCATION:Chainline Brewing Company\, 500 Urban Plz\, Kirkland\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-food
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Food & Drink
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
